Ans.1 = python is an interpreted, high level and general purpose programming language. 
 because it is easy to learn or easy to understand. It is interpreted some other languages 
 As we know python develop in C language and which will support anything like window 
 or linux that is gauranted by the developer. you can build webapps, write machine learning
 algorithms, embedded system and a lot of things . 

Ans.2 = In python, there is no need to define the types of variables. It allows to directly
 use the variables as its type-checking will be done during the execution of the program. 
 The interpreter checks the program line-by-line and also examines the data type of the variable. 

Ans.3 = pros                              
 1.It is easy to learn and easy to code
 2.Python is a very readable language because of its syntax.
 3.Python supports procedure-oriented programming and object oriented programming. Programs built 
   around object the merges data and functionality in object-oriented programming
 4.Python requires very less coding when compared to other programming languages to complete a
   simple task
 5.We can embed Python within C/C++ programs to give 'scripting' capabilities for program's users.

 Cons. 
 1. Python execution results are a bit slow as the code executed line by line.
 2. Python is not suitable to use under the limited memory restrictions. Python 
    structures need more memory space.
 3. Database layers are less comparative when compared with standard database layers
     ODBC and JDBC.
 4. Python is not so strong with mobile computing
 5. Python is not easy to test

Ans.4 = python is used for different domains such as Artificial Intelligence, machine learning,
 Data scientist, Data Analyst , developing websites and software, task Automation, web server 
 side development but It is not considered ideal for mobile app development and game development 
 due to the consumption of more memory and its slow processing speed while compared to other
 programming languages.

Ans.5 = In python there is no command or no need to decalre a variable. Variables is only a name
  given to a memory location, all the operations done on the variable effects that memory location.
 we declare only the assign value we put into the variable like (int, str, float) and after we
 check which type of data we assign in variable using "type" function. 

