Ans. 7 = The default data type of the value that has been taken as an input using input() function
  is "string". By default, input returns a string. So the name and age will be stored as strings. 

Ans.8 = In python type casting means that when we convert one data type to another data type like
 int to float, float to int etc 
 for example =
a = int("10")
b = float("10.0")
casted_a = float(a)
casted_b = int(b)
print(casted_a)
print(casted_b)

